3.1. Confronting nuclear forces with empirical constraints
Figure 2 (left) illustrates the nuclear EOS at zero temperature as a function of density n
"for a representative set of isospin asymmetries δ = (nn − np)/n, where nn (np) is the
neutron (proton) number density. Several general observations can be gleaned. Nuclear"
"interactions are much stronger in SNM compared to PNM, which is closer to the free Fermi"
"gas (FFG, solid lines). Consequently, the uncertainties are larger in SNM, especially for"
"densities n & n0. In PNM they are well controlled for n . n0, and a wide range of"
